So, what is GraphQL?

GraphQL is a query language for APIs, developed by Facebook, and it gives clients the power to ask for exactly the data they needâ€”nothing more, nothing less. Unlike REST, where you may overfetch or underfetch data, GraphQL makes data fetching flexible and efficient.

Think of GraphQL like ordering food at a restaurant. With REST, you get a fixed menu item with fries, drink, and a burger, even if you only wanted the burger. With GraphQL, you can customize your order: â€œJust give me the burger and hold the fries.â€

In this episode, weâ€™ll set up our very first GraphQL server using Node.js and Apollo Server. Letâ€™s jump in!â€*

