ğŸ™ Narration Script
*"Welcome back to our GraphQL tutorial series!

In Episode 1, we learned how to fetch a list of books with GraphQL queries. But what if you donâ€™t want all the books? What if you only want a specific book by its title?

Thatâ€™s where arguments come in.

Arguments in GraphQL allow us to pass values into our queries so that the server can respond with exactly what we want. Itâ€™s just like giving a filter or a search term.

Letâ€™s go ahead and add query arguments to our schema so we can fetch a single book by title."*

