ğŸ“º Episode 3: Mutations in GraphQL (Create, Update, Delete)
Goal: Learn how to create, update, and delete data using GraphQL mutations.

ğŸ™ Narration Script
*"Welcome back to the GraphQL tutorial series!

So far, weâ€™ve learned how to fetch data using queries. But real-world apps arenâ€™t just about reading data â€” we also need to create, update, and delete things.

Thatâ€™s where mutations come in.

In GraphQL, queries are for reading, while mutations are for writing. Think of them like POST, PUT, and DELETE in REST, but much more flexible.

In this episode, weâ€™re going to add mutations to our schema so that we can add a new book, update a book, and delete a book. Letâ€™s jump right into it!"*

ğŸ“š Lesson Structure
Intro â€“ Recap queries & arguments, introduce mutations.

Explanation â€“ Mutations vs queries, input arguments, return types.

Demo â€“ Implement addBook, updateBook, deleteBook.

Recap â€“ CRUD with GraphQL mutations.

ğŸ’» Demo (Code to Copy-Paste)
Step 1: Update index.js
Replace with:

const { ApolloServer, gql } = require('apollo-server');

// Schema
const typeDefs = gql`
  type Book {
    title: String
    author: String
  }

  type Query {
    books: [Book]
    book(title: String!): Book
  }

  type Mutation {
    addBook(title: String!, author: String!): Book
    updateBook(title: String!, newAuthor: String!): Book
    deleteBook(title: String!): String
  }
`;

// Sample data
let books = [
  { title: "The Hobbit", author: "J.R.R. Tolkien" },
  { title: "1984", author: "George Orwell" },
  { title: "Clean Code", author: "Robert C. Martin" }
];

// Resolvers
const resolvers = {
  Query: {
    books: () => books,
    book: (_, args) => books.find(b => b.title === args.title),
  },
  Mutation: {
    addBook: (_, { title, author }) => {
      const newBook = { title, author };
      books.push(newBook);
      return newBook;
    },
    updateBook: (_, { title, newAuthor }) => {
      const book = books.find(b => b.title === title);
      if (!book) throw new Error("Book not found");
      book.author = newAuthor;
      return book;
    },
    deleteBook: (_, { title }) => {
      const index = books.findIndex(b => b.title === title);
      if (index === -1) throw new Error("Book not found");
      books.splice(index, 1);
      return `${title} was deleted successfully.`;
    }
  }
};

// Apollo Server
const server = new ApolloServer({ typeDefs, resolvers });

server.listen().then(({ url }) => {
  console.log(`ğŸš€ Server ready at ${url}`);
});
Step 2: Restart server
node index.js
Step 3: Test Mutations in Playground
âœ… Add a book:

mutation {
  addBook(title: "Dune", author: "Frank Herbert") {
    title
    author
  }
}
âœ… Update a book:

mutation {
  updateBook(title: "1984", newAuthor: "Eric Arthur Blair") {
    title
    author
  }
}
âœ… Delete a book:

mutation {
  deleteBook(title: "Clean Code")
}
âœ… Query all books after changes:

query {
  books {
    title
    author
  }
}
