ğŸ“º Episode 5 (Upgraded): Input Validation & Error Handling with MySQL
Goal: Prevent invalid or duplicate data and return proper errors in GraphQL.

ğŸ™ Narration Script
*"Welcome back to the GraphQL series!

In Episode 4, we built full CRUD functionality â€” we could add, read, update, and delete books from MySQL. Thatâ€™s powerful, but thereâ€™s still a problem: what happens if users send bad data?

For example, what if they try to add a book without a title? Or what if they try to update a book that doesnâ€™t exist? Right now, our API would just fail silently or insert junk data.

Today, weâ€™ll fix that by adding input validation and error handling. This is how we make our GraphQL API safe and reliable in real-world applications."*

ğŸ“š Lesson Structure
Intro â€“ Recap CRUD, problem of invalid input.

Validation Rules â€“ Examples: required fields, duplicates.

Error Handling â€“ Use GraphQL ApolloError for meaningful messages.

Demo â€“ Add validation to addBook, updateBook, and deleteBook.

Recap â€“ Our API now rejects bad data gracefully.

ğŸ’» Step 1: Import ApolloError
const { ApolloServer, gql, ApolloError } = require("apollo-server");
ğŸ’» Step 2: Add Validation to Mutations
const resolvers = {
  Query: {
    books: async () => {
      const [rows] = await pool.query("SELECT * FROM books");
      return rows;
    },
    book: async (_, { id }) => {
      const [rows] = await pool.query("SELECT * FROM books WHERE id = ?", [id]);
      if (rows.length === 0) {
        throw new ApolloError(`Book with ID ${id} not found`, "BOOK_NOT_FOUND");
      }
      return rows[0];
    }
  },

  Mutation: {
    addBook: async (_, { input }) => {
      const { title, author } = input;

      if (!title || !author) {
        throw new ApolloError("Title and author are required", "BAD_USER_INPUT");
      }

      // Check for duplicate title
      const [existing] = await pool.query("SELECT * FROM books WHERE title = ?", [title]);
      if (existing.length > 0) {
        throw new ApolloError("A book with this title already exists", "DUPLICATE_BOOK");
      }

      const [result] = await pool.query(
        "INSERT INTO books (title, author) VALUES (?, ?)",
        [title, author]
      );

      return { id: result.insertId, title, author };
    },

    updateBook: async (_, { input }) => {
      const { id, title, author } = input;

      const [existing] = await pool.query("SELECT * FROM books WHERE id = ?", [id]);
      if (existing.length === 0) {
        throw new ApolloError(`Book with ID ${id} not found`, "BOOK_NOT_FOUND");
      }

      const newTitle = title || existing[0].title;
      const newAuthor = author || existing[0].author;

      await pool.query("UPDATE books SET title = ?, author = ? WHERE id = ?", [
        newTitle,
        newAuthor,
        id
      ]);

      return { id, title: newTitle, author: newAuthor };
    },

    deleteBook: async (_, { id }) => {
      const [result] = await pool.query("DELETE FROM books WHERE id = ?", [id]);
      if (result.affectedRows === 0) {
        throw new ApolloError(`Book with ID ${id} not found`, "BOOK_NOT_FOUND");
      }
      return true;
    }
  }
};
