ğŸ“º Episode 7: Authentication & Authorization in GraphQL with MySQL
Goal: Add user accounts with authentication (JWT) and authorization rules so only logged-in users can add/update/delete data.

ğŸ™ Narration Script
*"Welcome back!

Our GraphQL API can now handle relationships like books and authors, but right now, anyone can add, update, or delete data. Thatâ€™s not safe.

In this episode, weâ€™ll add authentication (logging in users with JWT) and authorization (restricting certain operations).

Hereâ€™s what weâ€™ll do step by step:

Create a users table in MySQL.

Add registration and login mutations.

Generate JWT tokens on login.

Protect mutations so only authenticated users can make changes.

Letâ€™s get started!"*

ğŸ“š Lesson Structure
Intro â€“ Why security matters.

Database Setup â€“ Users table.

Auth Mutations â€“ Register & login with JWT.

Protect Mutations â€“ Middleware for authentication.

Demo â€“ Try adding books without and with a token.

Recap â€“ Secure GraphQL API.

ğŸ’» Step 1: Install Dependencies
npm install jsonwebtoken bcrypt
ğŸ’» Step 2: Create Users Table
CREATE TABLE users (
  id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
  username VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
