ğŸ“º Episode 8: Role-Based Authorization in GraphQL with MySQL
Goal: Extend authentication to include roles (e.g., USER, ADMIN) and enforce role-based access to certain mutations.

ğŸ™ Narration Script
*"Welcome back!

In the last episode, we secured our GraphQL API with JWT authentication, so only logged-in users can add books or authors. But in real-world apps, not all users are equal.

For example:

A regular user might be allowed to add books.

An admin should be able to delete books or authors.

Thatâ€™s where Role-Based Authorization (RBAC) comes in.

Today, weâ€™ll:

Extend our users table to include a role.

Assign roles during registration.

Update our resolvers to check if the logged-in user has the right role.

Letâ€™s build it!"*

ğŸ“š Lesson Structure
Intro â€“ Why roles are important.

Database Update â€“ Add role column.

Schema Update â€“ Expose roles in User.

Resolvers â€“ Restrict dangerous actions to admins.

Demo â€“ Try deleting a book as user vs admin.

Recap â€“ Secure, role-aware GraphQL API.

ğŸ’» Step 1: Update Database
ALTER TABLE users ADD COLUMN role ENUM('USER', 'ADMIN') DEFAULT 'USER';
ğŸ’» Step 2: Update Schema
const typeDefs = gql`
  enum Role {
    USER
    ADMIN
  }

  type User {
    id: ID!
    username: String!
    role: Role!
  }

  type AuthPayload {
    token: String!
    user: User!
  }

  type Author {
    id: ID!
    name: String!
    books: [Book!]!
  }

  type Book {
    id: ID!
    title: String!
    author: Author!
  }

  input RegisterInput {
    username: String!
    password: String!
    role: Role
  }

  input LoginInput {
    username: String!
    password: String!
  }

  input AddAuthorInput {
    name: String!
  }

  input AddBookInput {
    title: String!
    authorId: ID!
  }

  type Query {
    books: [Book!]!
    authors: [Author!]!
    book(id: ID!): Book
    author(id: ID!): Author
    me: User
  }

  type Mutation {
    register(input: RegisterInput!): User!
    login(input: LoginInput!): AuthPayload!

    addAuthor(input: AddAuthorInput!): Author!
    addBook(input: AddBookInput!): Book!
    deleteBook(id: ID!): Boolean!
  }
`;
ğŸ’» Step 3: Update Resolvers
const resolvers = {
  Query: {
    books: async () => {
      const [rows] = await pool.query("SELECT * FROM books");
      return rows;
    },
    authors: async () => {
      const [rows] = await pool.query("SELECT * FROM authors");
      return rows;
    },
    book: async (_, { id }) => {
      const [rows] = await pool.query("SELECT * FROM books WHERE id = ?", [id]);
      return rows[0];
    },
    author: async (_, { id }) => {
      const [rows] = await pool.query("SELECT * FROM authors WHERE id = ?", [id]);
      return rows[0];
    },
    me: (_, __, { user }) => {
      return user || null;
    }
  },

  Mutation: {
    register: async (_, { input }) => {
      const hashed = await bcrypt.hash(input.password, 10);
      const role = input.role || "USER";
      const [result] = await pool.query(
        "INSERT INTO users (username, password, role) VALUES (?, ?, ?)",
        [input.username, hashed, role]
      );
      return { id: result.insertId, username: input.username, role };
    },

    login: async (_, { input }) => {
      const [rows] = await pool.query("SELECT * FROM users WHERE username = ?", [
        input.username
      ]);
      if (rows.length === 0) throw new Error("User not found");

      const user = rows[0];
      const valid = await bcrypt.compare(input.password, user.password);
      if (!valid) throw new Error("Invalid password");

      const token = jwt.sign(
        { id: user.id, username: user.username, role: user.role },
        SECRET,
        { expiresIn: "1h" }
      );

      return {
        token,
        user: { id: user.id, username: user.username, role: user.role }
      };
    },

    addAuthor: async (_, { input }, { user }) => {
      if (!user) throw new Error("Not authenticated");
      const [result] = await pool.query("INSERT INTO authors (name) VALUES (?)", [
        input.name
      ]);
      return { id: result.insertId, name: input.name };
    },

    addBook: async (_, { input }, { user }) => {
      if (!user) throw new Error("Not authenticated");
      const { title, authorId } = input;
      const [result] = await pool.query(
        "INSERT INTO books (title, authorId) VALUES (?, ?)",
        [title, authorId]
      );
      return { id: result.insertId, title, authorId };
    },

    deleteBook: async (_, { id }, { user }) => {
      if (!user) throw new Error("Not authenticated");
      if (user.role !== "ADMIN") throw new Error("Not authorized");

      const [result] = await pool.query("DELETE FROM books WHERE id = ?", [id]);
      return result.affectedRows > 0;
    }
  },

  Book: {
    author: async (book) => {
      const [rows] = await pool.query("SELECT * FROM authors WHERE id = ?", [
        book.authorId
      ]);
      return rows[0];
    }
  },

  Author: {
    books: async (author) => {
      const [rows] = await pool.query("SELECT * FROM books WHERE authorId = ?", [
        author.id
      ]);
      return rows;
    }
  }
};
