ğŸ“º Episode 9: Pagination & Filtering in GraphQL with MySQL
Goal: Learn how to paginate results (limit/offset) and filter books/authors in queries.

ğŸ™ Narration Script
*"Welcome back!

So far, weâ€™ve built a secure API with authentication and role-based authorization. But imagine if our database had 10,000 books. If we just query books, GraphQL would try to fetch everything at once â€” which is slow and wasteful.

Thatâ€™s why we need pagination and filtering.

Today, weâ€™ll:

Add pagination parameters (limit, offset) to queries.

Add filtering, like searching books by title or authors by name.

Combine both for efficient queries.

Letâ€™s dive in!"*

ğŸ“š Lesson Structure
Intro â€“ Why pagination & filtering matter.

Schema Update â€“ Add pagination & filter arguments.

Resolvers â€“ Implement with MySQL queries.

Demo â€“ Paginate & filter in Apollo Sandbox.

