ğŸ“º Episode 10: Sorting & Ordering in GraphQL with MySQL
Goal:
Add sorting and ordering capabilities to our GraphQL queries â€” for example, sort books alphabetically or by creation date.

ğŸ™ Narration Script
*"Welcome back, GraphQL developers!

In the last episode, we learned how to paginate and filter data. That was awesome â€” but what if we want to sort our data too?

For example:

Show the newest books first.

List authors in alphabetical order.

Thatâ€™s what weâ€™ll do today.
Weâ€™ll add optional sorting arguments to our queries, and dynamically build MySQL queries based on them.

Letâ€™s jump in!"*

ğŸ“š Lesson Structure
Intro â€“ Why sorting improves UX and performance.

