ğŸ™ Narration Script
*"Welcome back, developers!

So far, weâ€™ve built a pretty powerful GraphQL API â€” it can query, filter, paginate, and even sort data from MySQL. But all of that still relies on polling â€” the client keeps asking for updates.

Wouldnâ€™t it be cooler if the server could push updates to the client automatically?

Thatâ€™s where GraphQL Subscriptions come in.

Today, weâ€™ll use Apollo Server with WebSockets to broadcast events when new books are added, so connected clients receive live updates â€” no refresh needed.

